1. REQUIREMENTS
=================

	* Eterm 0.9.6

2. ARCH INSTALL
=================

	The easiest way to install eterm-themes on Arch Linux is via the Arch User Repositories (AUR).

	Using `yay` or your AUR helper of choice, do the following:

	yay -S eterm-themes

	However, if you have cloned this repository from github, you can still install eterm-themes from the Arch AUR by doing the following:

	cd eterm-themes/_archlinux
	makepkg -si

3. ARCH UNINSTALL
=================

	To remove the package:

	yay -Rsu eterm-themes

3. MANUAL INSTALL
=================

	To manually install the themes, do the following:

	cd eterm-themes
	mkdir -p /usr/share/Eterm/themes
	cp -rv --preserve=mode themes/* /usr/share/Eterm/themes/

